    aboutKicker: 'Gynecologist’s View',
    aboutTitle: 'Gynecologist’s View',
    aboutText: [
      '“Gynecology, for me, is more than a specialty; it means being able to look at a woman’s life as a whole. In the examination room and in the operating room, my priority is to understand what the woman is experiencing, state clearly what the evidence shows, and remain honest where evidence is not sufficient.',
      'Surgery is not a one-person task; it is the shared work of a well-prepared team, of people who hear one another, and of hands that care for the same woman with the same attention. The trust built in the operating room over years includes technical skill, but also collaboration, mutual respect and commitment to the work being done.',
      'I continue the surgical discipline that comes from obstetrics and gynecology and gynecologic oncology surgery together with my active research in minimally invasive surgery, vaginal aesthetics, HPV, deep endometriosis, the vaginal microbiota and ERAS protocols.',
      'At Istinye University Liv Hospital Topkapı, I care for women, perform surgery and conduct research as an Assistant Professor. My aim is to translate information into language the woman in front of me can understand, and to plan treatment not only through medical indicators, but also by taking her fears, privacy concerns and expectations into account.”',
    ],
