        body: ["Vaginal tightening is a phrase consumed very quickly on the internet, but in a medical consultation the first step is to understand what the actual complaint is. Laxity sensation, gas leakage, urinary incontinence, comfort during intercourse, birth tears and the pelvic floor are all separate topics.", "For some patients surgery may be discussed, while for others pelvic floor support, lubricants, local treatments, dilators or an infection-and-dryness assessment is the more appropriate first step. Since excessive narrowing of the vaginal canal can cause pain and intercourse difficulty, the goal should not be tight but functional and comfortable.", "For this reason, the decision is never made without an examination. When the complaint is correctly named, unnecessary procedures are avoided and a more realistic plan can be made for the patient who can genuinely benefit."],
